'''TIE staging areas''' were small [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] space bases built by the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]]. After the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]], the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] attacked several Imperial vessels in order to keep enemy pursuers off of their trail after [[Yavin 4/Legends|Yavin 4]] was abandoned. Several of these vessels lost a great deal of [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighters]] as a result of these battles with the Rebels, so numerous TIE staging areas were built across the galaxy in order to resupply these ships within a short period of time.<ref name="TOD B-wing">''[[Star Wars: X-Wing Tour of Duty: B-Wing]]''</ref>

During the events preceding the creation of [[Echo Base/Legends|Echo Base]] on [[Hoth/Legends|Hoth]], the Rebel pilot [[Keyan Farlander/Legends|Keyan Farlander]] was sent to [[Attack on a TIE staging area|destroy]] one of these bases near [[Yunkor IX]].<ref name="TOD B-wing" /> He flew the newly-released [[A/SF-01 B-wing starfighter/Legends|B-wing starfighter]] in its first official combat mission against the Empire.<ref name="Sony B-wing">{{SonyCite|url=en_US/players/content.vm?id=66868&resource=features|text=Ships: B-Wing}}</ref> Farlander succeeded and destroyed the entire base.<ref name="TOD B-wing" />

